Kennedy starts the night off talking about Donald Trump and his signing on the Republican Loyalty pledge.

We've got 3 great guests on tonight's panel. Tom Shillue, Jedediah Bila, and Charles Cooke. They continue talking about Trump and his loyalty pledge. Kennedy seems sure Trump is going to take the nomination. Charles Cooke disagrees. After a quick commercial break the panel returns to talk MORE DEFLATE GATE! Hurray! Get out the confetti and streamers guys I think this may be the 1,000,000 time! Anyway - a judge has thrown out Brady's suspension. The panel discusses.

GREG GUTFELD, former host of Red Eye, is in studio to talk about a potential Biden bid. They move on to talking about the Hillary email scandal and someone from her campaign pleading the 5th in regards to the whole ordeal.

Our polished party panel returns to play FACT or FICTION. The topic, Carley Fiorna.

Kennedy hits to street to break some laws. On tonight's K-Walking Kennedy break some dumb state laws. BEN KISSEL arrives shortly after to talk about America's bloated prison population.

Nightcap: Mailbag. Here's a snippet, "Dear Kennedy. You suck and are so obnoxious. Shame on Fox for cramming you down our throats." -Ann Hughes
